    "5 This ANOVA showed a main effect of testimonies, F(1, 188) = 636.4, p < 0.001, Î· 2 p = 0.772; and no main effect for group, F(1, 188) = 0.104, p = 0.747, Î· 2 p = 0.001.",
    "However, and as we expected, we observed a Testimonies x Group interaction, F(1, 188) = 16.3, p < 0.001, Î· 2 p = 0.080.",
    "Subsequent post-hoc comparisons (Tukey correction) showed that, as we expected, participants in the Judgmentâ†’AIsupport group judged defendants in the incorrect cases as less guilty when the testimonies indicated innocence (M = 18.1, SD = 15.2, t(369) = -3.26, p = 0.007, d = -0.53) than did participants in the AIsupportâ†’Judgment group (M = 28.2, SD = 22.5).",
    "In addition, when the testimonies indicated guilt, the Judgmentâ†’AIsupport group judged the defendants in the incorrect cases to be more guilty (M = 79.8, SD = 15.7, t(369) = 2.83, p = 0.025, d = 0.48) than the AIsupportâ†’Judgment group (M = 70.8, SD = 21.0).",
    "These results indicate that participants in the Judgmentâ†’AIsupport group were more accurate in their judgments."
  ]
